column5: Though I would try this area for walleye last Saturday, lots of boats out.  Drove all around victoria harbor, sturgeon bay,hog bay and out near snake island. Not very exciting LOL!  I marked 2 fish on the screen and caught 1 small mouth on a Lindy rigged minnow.  The hunt for GBay walleye continues!  Sorry not very exciting report but was a beautiful fall day!
I haven't been up there in years. I heard the trough is great once they start staging. Any one else hooking up on fish?

Ya that's where all the boats were congregating, I saw 2 eye's caught, but marked nothing. So I don't know if they have already moved out of there or haven't showed yet.. my guess is they haven't showed yet. I was reading a temp of 47 all day so they should be starting I would think.
I agree...I would bet it hasn't happened yet. Good luck and we'll wait for the pics!
try earlier or later for the bite...it seems to shut off like a light switch up my way.
